C. sdc-config

	Display SDC board information, serial port mode setting and firmware
	update function.

	Display all SDC board info
		$ sdc-config -d
			ID0: model=SDC0880I, firmware=1.9, pci_bus=1, irq=16
			ID1: model=SDC4441LL, firmware=1.9, pci_bus=6, irq=19

	Display detail info
		$ sdc-config -D 1
			ID1: model=SDC4441LL, firmware=1.9, pci_bus=6, irq=19
				CONFIG(0):
					ver=x00, pid=3, /dev=sdc_config1
					brand=0, model=0
				UART(1):
					ver=x00, pid=4, /dev=ttyS4
					fifo=128, cap=rs232
				UART(2):
					ver=x00, pid=5, /dev=ttyS5
					fifo=128, cap=rs232
				UART(3):
					ver=x00, pid=6, /dev=ttyS6
					fifo=128, cap=rs422|rs485
				UART(4):
					ver=x00, pid=7, /dev=ttyS7
					fifo=128, cap=rs422|rs485
				DIO(5):
					ver=x00, pid=8, /dev=sdc_dio1
					cap=x03, nr_bank=2
						B0: nr_io=4, cap=input
						B1: nr_io=4, cap=output
				SPI(6):
					ver=x01, pid=9
					nr_device=1
						D0: type=3, nr_gpio=1;1, name=MCP25625, dev=can0

	Get serial port mode
		$ sudo sdc-config -S ttyS6 get
			ttyS6 config=rs485

	Set serial port mode 
		$ sudo sdc-config -S ttyS6 set rs422 term
			Set ttyS6 config success

	Update SDC firmware
